FBIS4-1471 "drafr083_b_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-083 Daily Report 28 Apr 1994 EAST AFRICA Tanzania Rwandan Ministers Apologize for Not Attending Talks Rwandan Ministers Apologize for Not Attending Talks EA2804212494 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network in Swahili 1700 GMT 28 Apr 94 EA2804212494 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network Swahili BFN [Text] The Government of Rwanda has apologized to President Ali Hasan Mwinyi for failing to attend the Rwanda peace talks in Arusha last weekend. In a message delivered to President Mwinyi today by the Rwanda minister of communications and transport, Andre Ntagerura, and the Rwanda Justice Minister Agnes Ntamabyariro, the Government of Rwanda apologized for the failure to attend the meeting, citing travel difficulties in Zaire and misinformation as the reasons for their delegation's absence. They called on the president to continue his efforts to reconcile the warring factions in Rwanda in keeping with the Arusha peace accord signed last year. President Mwinyi agreed to call for another meeting at a date to be announced later. Meanwhile, President Mwinyi held talks with the Belgium secretary of state for cooperation and development, Mr. Eric Derycke, on economic cooperation between the two countries and on the Government of Tanzania's efforts to resolve the political crisis in Rwanda.
